<div class="entry-content single-content">
	<div class="dpsp-post-pinterest-image-hidden" style="display: none;"><img width="150" height="150" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;150&#039;%20height=&#039;150&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%20150%20150&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" data-pin-media="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chewy-oatmeal-cookies-pin-3.jpg" alt="Top view of oatmeal cookies arranged on parchment paper and a plate, with the text &quot;chewy oatmeal cookies&quot; in bold lettering between the images." class="dpsp-post-pinterest-image-hidden-inner perfmatters-lazy" data-src="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chewy-oatmeal-cookies-pin-3-150x150.jpg" /></div><div class="dpsp-post-pinterest-image-hidden" style="display: none;"><img width="150" height="150" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;150&#039;%20height=&#039;150&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%20150%20150&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" data-pin-media="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chewy-oatmeal-cookies-pin-2.jpg" alt="Several oatmeal cookies are arranged on parchment paper with some oats scattered around. Text at the bottom reads &quot;chewy oatmeal cookies&quot; with a small lemon icon above the text." class="dpsp-post-pinterest-image-hidden-inner perfmatters-lazy" data-src="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chewy-oatmeal-cookies-pin-2-150x150.jpg" /></div><div class="dpsp-post-pinterest-image-hidden" style="display: none;"><img width="150" height="150" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;150&#039;%20height=&#039;150&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%20150%20150&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" data-pin-media="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chewy-oatmeal-cookies-pin-1.jpg" alt="A cooling rack with chewy oatmeal cookies arranged on top, some oats scattered nearby. A label reads &quot;chewy oatmeal cookies&quot; and &quot;joyfullymad.com&quot; at the bottom." class="dpsp-post-pinterest-image-hidden-inner  dpsp-post-pinterest-image-hidden-single perfmatters-lazy" data-src="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chewy-oatmeal-cookies-pin-1-150x150.jpg" /></div>
<p class="kt-adv-heading38457_c9b098-9d wp-block-kadence-advancedheading has-theme-palette-8-background-color has-background" data-kb-block="kb-adv-heading38457_c9b098-9d">These Chewy Oatmeal Cookies have<ins> a delicious blend of chewy oats, warm vanilla and earthy cinnamon. You can</ins> have a batch of these on the table in just half an hour - no chilling the dough or egg required. Sweet, satisfying and just a little old-fashioned, you'll soon be reaching for "just one more" after the first taste.&nbsp;</p><div class="wprm-recipe wprm-recipe-snippet wprm-recipe-template-jump-buttons"><a href="#recipe" data-recipe="38458" style="color: #333333;background-color: #ffffff;border-color: #333333;border-radius: 20px;padding: 5px 15px;" class="wprm-recipe-jump wprm-recipe-link wprm-jump-to-recipe-shortcode wprm-block-text-normal wprm-recipe-jump-inline-button wprm-recipe-link-inline-button wprm-color-accent"><span class="wprm-recipe-icon wprm-recipe-jump-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewbox="0 0 24 24"><g class="nc-icon-wrapper" fill="#333333"><path data-color="color-2" d="M9,2h6c0.6,0,1-0.4,1-1s-0.4-1-1-1H9C8.4,0,8,0.4,8,1S8.4,2,9,2z"></path> <path fill="#333333" d="M16,11V5c0-0.6-0.4-1-1-1H9C8.4,4,8,4.4,8,5v6H1.9L12,23.6L22.1,11H16z"></path></g></svg></span> Jump to Recipe</a>
</div><!-- [element-39028] -->
<p class="has-text-align-center has-small-font-size">This post contains affiliate links. </p>
<!-- [/element-39028] -->



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1198" height="1800" fetchpriority="high" src="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-14.jpg" alt="A stack of six oatmeal cookies sits on a white plate, with a bottle of milk and more cookies blurred in the background." data-skip-lazy class="wp-image-38392" srcset="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-14.jpg 1198w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-14-660x992.jpg 660w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-14-735x1104.jpg 735w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-14-768x1154.jpg 768w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-14-1022x1536.jpg 1022w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-14-360x541.jpg 360w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-14-180x270.jpg 180w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-14-720x1082.jpg 720w" sizes="(max-width: 1198px) 100vw, 1198px" data-pin-media="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-14.jpg"></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-soft-oatmeal-cookies-with-cinnamon">Soft Oatmeal Cookies with Cinnamon</h2>



<p>If you ask me, a good oatmeal cookie doesn't need frosting, raisins, chocolate chips or <em>anything</em> piled on top. So long as the texture is right and the flavor is balanced, these cookies are a real treat. </p>



<p>This recipe took multiple rounds to get them right, but the&nbsp;warm cinnamon and vanilla aromas while they bake always makes my mouth water.</p>



<p>Brown sugar is one of the key ingredients here, giving the oatmeal cookies a rich, almost caramel-like sweetness, and also helping keep them soft. And then you have the oats, which make them more filling than simple sugar cookies. A touch of vanilla and a pinch of cinnamon add those nostalgic flavors home baking is all about.</p>



<p>Bake a batch of these chewy oatmeal cookies anytime to pair with anything from a cold glass of milk to a <a href="https://joyfullymad.com/easy-homemade-pumpkin-spice-latte-recipe/"><strong>pumpkin spice latte</strong></a> or cup of tea. They're just as good for cookie trays at the holidays as they are for a mid-morning snack in summertime.</p>


<div class="kb-row-layout-wrap kb-row-layout-id38457_37c8a1-09 alignnone wp-block-kadence-rowlayout"><div class="kt-row-column-wrap kt-has-1-columns kt-row-layout-equal kt-tab-layout-inherit kt-mobile-layout-row kt-row-valign-top">

<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column38457_b11897-28"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col"><h2 class="kt-adv-heading38457_340671-16 wp-block-kadence-advancedheading kt-adv-heading-has-icon has-theme-palette8-background-color has-background" data-kb-block="kb-adv-heading38457_340671-16"><span class="kb-svg-icon-wrap kb-adv-heading-icon kb-svg-icon-fas_check-circle kb-adv-heading-icon-side-left"><svg viewbox="0 0 512 512" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M504 256c0 136.967-111.033 248-248 248S8 392.967 8 256 119.033 8 256 8s248 111.033 248 248zM227.314 387.314l184-184c6.248-6.248 6.248-16.379 0-22.627l-22.627-22.627c-6.248-6.249-16.379-6.249-22.628 0L216 308.118l-70.059-70.059c-6.248-6.248-16.379-6.248-22.628 0l-22.627 22.627c-6.248 6.248-6.248 16.379 0 22.627l104 104c6.249 6.249 16.379 6.249 22.628.001z"></path></svg></span><span class="kb-adv-text-inner">Why You'll Love This Recipe</span></h2>


<p style="padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--40);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--40)">These chewy oatmeal cookies make for a delicious treat! </p>



<ul style="padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--60);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--60)" class="wp-block-list">
<li style="margin-right:0;margin-left:0"><strong>Soft and chewy texture:</strong> These cookies have a tender center, lightly crisp edges and plenty of chew from the old-fashioned oats.</li>



<li><strong>Brown sugar flavor: </strong>Using only brown sugar gives them a richer sweetness and a slightly caramel-like taste that suits this type of cookie.</li>



<li><strong>Simple pantry ingredients:</strong> There's nothing unusual here, just butter, flour, oats, brown sugar and a few baking staples.</li>



<li><strong>They keep for days:</strong> These soften a little more over time and will last for up to 5 days, or you can freeze baked cookies or balls of dough for baking later. (Well, possibly not in this house with hungry boys around!)</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

</div></div>


<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;1200&#039;%20height=&#039;1800&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%201200%201800&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Bowls containing brown sugar, unsalted butter, vanilla extract, cornstarch, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda, all-purpose flour, and old fashioned oats on a white surface." class="wp-image-38411 perfmatters-lazy" data-pin-media="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chewy-oatmeal-cookies.jpg" data-src="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chewy-oatmeal-cookies.jpg" data-srcset="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chewy-oatmeal-cookies.jpg 1200w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chewy-oatmeal-cookies-660x990.jpg 660w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chewy-oatmeal-cookies-735x1103.jpg 735w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chewy-oatmeal-cookies-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chewy-oatmeal-cookies-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chewy-oatmeal-cookies-720x1080.jpg 720w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chewy-oatmeal-cookies-360x540.jpg 360w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chewy-oatmeal-cookies-180x270.jpg 180w" data-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Ingredients</h2>



<p>You'll need <strong>unsalted butter</strong> as the base for the cookie dough. If needed, you can use margarine, but I always find butter gives the best flavor. <strong>Brown sugar</strong> is the only sugar I tested here, but I wouldn't swap it for white sugar. It brings more moisture to the dough, which you need to give these cookies their chewy texture and deeper sweetness.</p>


<div class="kb-row-layout-wrap kb-row-layout-id38457_ad2cf4-ac alignnone wp-block-kadence-rowlayout"><div class="kt-row-column-wrap kt-has-1-columns kt-row-layout-equal kt-tab-layout-inherit kt-mobile-layout-row kt-row-valign-middle">

<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column38457_cdc282-83"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<p>Make sure the butter has softened before you start. This helps it cream properly with the brown sugar to give your cookies an even texture.&nbsp;</p>
</div></div>

</div></div>


<p><strong>Vanilla extract</strong> rounds out the flavor and takes the edge off the sweetness - make sure you're using pure vanilla extract for the best taste. <strong>All-purpose flour</strong> forms the structure of the dough, while <strong>cornstarch</strong> helps keep the cookies soft and tender.&nbsp;</p>



<p><strong>Baking powder and baking soda</strong> are both important in this recipe, so don't reduce or skip either one. They help the cookies rise slightly and prevent a dense texture. <strong>Cinnamon</strong> gives the dough a warm flavor that works well with the oats and brown sugar, and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> keeps the sweetness in check and helps the whole cookie taste more balanced.</p>



<p>And finally, the star ingredient - <strong>old fashioned oats</strong> - are what give these cookies their hearty texture and chew.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="798" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;1200&#039;%20height=&#039;798&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%201200%20798&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="A close-up of an oatmeal cookie on parchment paper, with more cookies blurred in the background." class="wp-image-38387 perfmatters-lazy" data-pin-media="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-9.jpg" data-src="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-9.jpg" data-srcset="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-9.jpg 1200w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-9-660x439.jpg 660w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-9-735x489.jpg 735w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-9-768x511.jpg 768w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-9-720x479.jpg 720w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-9-360x239.jpg 360w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-9-180x120.jpg 180w" data-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-how-to-make-chewy-oatmeal-cookies">How to Make Chewy Oatmeal Cookies</h2>



<p>Baking these cookies is a breeze! You won't even need to chill the dough, although you totally can if you need some time between mixing the dough and baking the cookies. (If you do chill it, let the dough sit out for 15 minutes or so before you start forming cookie dough balls - this makes the dough easier to handle).</p>


<div class="kb-row-layout-wrap kb-row-layout-id38457_e94b92-48 alignnone wp-block-kadence-rowlayout"><div class="kt-row-column-wrap kt-has-2-columns kt-row-layout-equal kt-tab-layout-inherit kt-mobile-layout-equal kt-row-valign-top">

<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column38457_35914c-c9"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1198" height="1800" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;1198&#039;%20height=&#039;1800&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%201198%201800&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="A glass bowl with brown sugar, butter, and vanilla, surrounded by small bowls of oats, flour, baking soda, and spices on a white surface." class="wp-image-38380 perfmatters-lazy" data-pin-media="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-2.jpg" data-src="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-2.jpg" data-srcset="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-2.jpg 1198w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-2-660x992.jpg 660w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-2-735x1104.jpg 735w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-2-768x1154.jpg 768w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-2-1022x1536.jpg 1022w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-2-360x541.jpg 360w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-2-180x270.jpg 180w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-2-720x1082.jpg 720w" data-sizes="(max-width: 1198px) 100vw, 1198px" /></figure>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column38457_396aa1-ca"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1198" height="1800" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;1198&#039;%20height=&#039;1800&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%201198%201800&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="A glass mixing bowl with flour, cinnamon, and sugar on top of creamed butter, surrounded by bowls of oats, baking soda, and salt on a white surface." class="wp-image-38381 perfmatters-lazy" data-pin-media="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-3.jpg" data-src="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-3.jpg" data-srcset="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-3.jpg 1198w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-3-660x992.jpg 660w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-3-735x1104.jpg 735w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-3-768x1154.jpg 768w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-3-1022x1536.jpg 1022w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-3-360x541.jpg 360w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-3-180x270.jpg 180w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-3-720x1082.jpg 720w" data-sizes="(max-width: 1198px) 100vw, 1198px" /></figure>
</div></div>

</div></div>

<div class="kb-row-layout-wrap kb-row-layout-id38457_e80f06-c1 alignnone wp-block-kadence-rowlayout"><div class="kt-row-column-wrap kt-has-2-columns kt-row-layout-equal kt-tab-layout-inherit kt-mobile-layout-row kt-row-valign-top">

<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column38457_2b5e8f-50"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li>Cream together the softened butter, brown sugar and vanilla extract.</li>
</ol>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column38457_04a078-4c"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<ol start="2" class="wp-block-list">
<li>Mix in the flour, cornstarch, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt, to form a dough.</li>
</ol>
</div></div>

</div></div>

<div class="kb-row-layout-wrap kb-row-layout-id38457_173f9e-8f alignnone wp-block-kadence-rowlayout"><div class="kt-row-column-wrap kt-has-2-columns kt-row-layout-equal kt-tab-layout-inherit kt-mobile-layout-equal kt-row-valign-top">

<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column38457_b93b9d-bd"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1198" height="1800" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;1198&#039;%20height=&#039;1800&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%201198%201800&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="A glass bowl containing partially mixed cookie dough and oats sits on a white surface, surrounded by empty white dishes and a small wooden bowl with salt." class="wp-image-38382 perfmatters-lazy" data-pin-media="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-4.jpg" data-src="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-4.jpg" data-srcset="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-4.jpg 1198w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-4-660x992.jpg 660w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-4-735x1104.jpg 735w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-4-768x1154.jpg 768w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-4-1022x1536.jpg 1022w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-4-360x541.jpg 360w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-4-180x270.jpg 180w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-4-720x1082.jpg 720w" data-sizes="(max-width: 1198px) 100vw, 1198px" /></figure>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column38457_bf7de1-f4"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1198" height="1800" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;1198&#039;%20height=&#039;1800&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%201198%201800&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="A glass bowl filled with oatmeal cookie dough sits on a white surface, surrounded by empty white bowls and a small wooden bowl of salt." class="wp-image-38383 perfmatters-lazy" data-pin-media="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-5.jpg" data-src="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-5.jpg" data-srcset="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-5.jpg 1198w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-5-660x992.jpg 660w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-5-735x1104.jpg 735w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-5-768x1154.jpg 768w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-5-1022x1536.jpg 1022w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-5-360x541.jpg 360w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-5-180x270.jpg 180w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-5-720x1082.jpg 720w" data-sizes="(max-width: 1198px) 100vw, 1198px" /></figure>
</div></div>

</div></div>

<div class="kb-row-layout-wrap kb-row-layout-id38457_c976d7-04 alignnone wp-block-kadence-rowlayout"><div class="kt-row-column-wrap kt-has-2-columns kt-row-layout-equal kt-tab-layout-inherit kt-mobile-layout-row kt-row-valign-top">

<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column38457_960eb6-02"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<ol start="3" class="wp-block-list">
<li>Fold in the oats.</li>
</ol>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column38457_662329-31"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<ol start="4" class="wp-block-list">
<li>The dough will be chunky -&nbsp;make sure the oats are well-distributed. </li>
</ol>
</div></div>

</div></div>

<div class="kb-row-layout-wrap kb-row-layout-id38457_baff67-28 alignnone wp-block-kadence-rowlayout"><div class="kt-row-column-wrap kt-has-2-columns kt-row-layout-equal kt-tab-layout-inherit kt-mobile-layout-equal kt-row-valign-top">

<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column38457_c34c84-80"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1198" height="1800" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;1198&#039;%20height=&#039;1800&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%201198%201800&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Six scoops of cookie dough are arranged on a parchment-lined baking sheet, ready to be baked." class="wp-image-38384 perfmatters-lazy" data-pin-media="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-6.jpg" data-src="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-6.jpg" data-srcset="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-6.jpg 1198w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-6-660x992.jpg 660w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-6-735x1104.jpg 735w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-6-768x1154.jpg 768w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-6-1022x1536.jpg 1022w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-6-360x541.jpg 360w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-6-180x270.jpg 180w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-6-720x1082.jpg 720w" data-sizes="(max-width: 1198px) 100vw, 1198px" /></figure>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column38457_5bf94c-26"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1198" height="1800" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;1198&#039;%20height=&#039;1800&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%201198%201800&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Six oatmeal cookies arranged in two columns on a parchment-lined baking sheet, viewed from above on a marble surface." class="wp-image-38385 perfmatters-lazy" data-pin-media="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-7.jpg" data-src="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-7.jpg" data-srcset="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-7.jpg 1198w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-7-660x992.jpg 660w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-7-735x1104.jpg 735w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-7-768x1154.jpg 768w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-7-1022x1536.jpg 1022w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-7-360x541.jpg 360w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-7-180x270.jpg 180w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-7-720x1082.jpg 720w" data-sizes="(max-width: 1198px) 100vw, 1198px" /></figure>
</div></div>

</div></div>

<div class="kb-row-layout-wrap kb-row-layout-id38457_1056f1-46 alignnone wp-block-kadence-rowlayout"><div class="kt-row-column-wrap kt-has-2-columns kt-row-layout-equal kt-tab-layout-inherit kt-mobile-layout-row kt-row-valign-top">

<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column38457_e9d496-b9"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<ol start="5" class="wp-block-list">
<li>Scoop cookie dough balls and space them out on a <a class="tasty-link" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-tasty-links-no-disclosure href="https://amzn.to/2S57fGV">parchment paper</a> lined <a class="tasty-link" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-tasty-links-no-disclosure href="https://amzn.to/2yXMkOh">baking sheet</a>. Bake the chewy oatmeal cookies until golden brown.</li>
</ol>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column38457_4db94f-8b"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<ol start="6" class="wp-block-list">
<li>Let them cool for a few minutes on the <a class="tasty-link" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-tasty-links-no-disclosure href="https://amzn.to/2yXMkOh">baking sheet</a>, then transfer them onto a cooling rack to cool completely.&nbsp;</li>
</ol>
</div></div>

</div></div>

<div class="kb-row-layout-wrap kb-row-layout-id38457_6ceacd-02 alignnone wp-block-kadence-rowlayout"><div class="kt-row-column-wrap kt-has-1-columns kt-row-layout-equal kt-tab-layout-inherit kt-mobile-layout-row kt-row-valign-middle">

<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column38457_f306aa-90"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<p>These cookies come together quickly, but don't be tempted to skip the cooling step. Cookies like this and <a href="https://joyfullymad.com/pumpkin-oatmeal-cookies/"><strong>pumpkin oatmeal cookies</strong></a> can be fragile right out of the oven and leaving them on the baking sheet for a few minutes makes a big difference. If you try to move them too soon, they're more likely to fall apart.</p>
</div></div>

</div></div>


<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1197" height="1800" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;1197&#039;%20height=&#039;1800&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%201197%201800&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Oatmeal cookies cooling on a black wire rack, with a few cookies and oats scattered on white plates and the white surface around them." class="wp-image-38386 perfmatters-lazy" data-pin-media="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-8.jpg" data-src="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-8.jpg" data-srcset="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-8.jpg 1197w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-8-660x992.jpg 660w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-8-735x1105.jpg 735w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-8-768x1155.jpg 768w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-8-1021x1536.jpg 1021w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-8-360x541.jpg 360w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-8-180x271.jpg 180w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-8-720x1083.jpg 720w" data-sizes="(max-width: 1197px) 100vw, 1197px" /></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Tips for Success</h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Use softened butter. </strong>If the butter's too cold, it won't cream properly with the sugar and the dough won't mix as smoothly.</li>



<li><strong>Don't swap the sugar. </strong>Brown sugar or a <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0FBZB3PLX?th=1">brown sugar alternative</a> adds moisture as well as sweetness, and that matters for the final texture.</li>



<li><strong>Use a pair of baking sheets if you have them.</strong> That way you can keep going without waiting for one hot tray to cool between batches.</li>



<li><strong>Watch the bottoms. </strong>The cookies are done when the bottoms are lightly golden, which usually takes 10 to 12 minutes, depending on your oven.</li>
</ul>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1198" height="1800" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;1198&#039;%20height=&#039;1800&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%201198%201800&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="A plate of oatmeal cookies arranged in a circle, with additional cookies on small plates and scattered oats on a white surface." class="wp-image-38389 perfmatters-lazy" data-pin-media="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-11.jpg" data-src="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-11.jpg" data-srcset="https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-11.jpg 1198w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-11-660x992.jpg 660w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-11-735x1104.jpg 735w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-11-768x1154.jpg 768w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-11-1022x1536.jpg 1022w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-11-360x541.jpg 360w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-11-180x270.jpg 180w, https://joyfullymad.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Chewy-Oatmeal-Cookies-11-720x1082.jpg 720w" data-sizes="(max-width: 1198px) 100vw, 1198px" /></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">FAQ</h2>



<div class="schema-faq wp-block-yoast-faq-block"><div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1738276414452"><strong class="schema-faq-question">How should I store soft oatmeal cookies?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Store them in an airtight container at room temperature for 4 to 5 days for the best texture.&nbsp;</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1777427833485"><strong class="schema-faq-question">Can I freeze them?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Yes. Freeze the scooped dough balls on a parchment-lined baking sheet until firm, then transfer them to a freezer bag or airtight container for up to 3 months. Bake from frozen and add 1 to 3 minutes to the baking time. You can also freeze fully baked cookies once cooled, with parchment between layers so they don't stick. For cookies like these though, I prefer freezing the unbaked dough, otherwise they won't thaw out as chewy.</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1777427834563"><strong class="schema-faq-question">Can I use quick oats?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">I like to use old-fashioned oats, which are also known as rolled oats. If you want to try quick oats, you may need a little more but keep the total under 3 cups for the best result. Quick oats are thinner and absorb more moisture, while old-fashioned oats will give a chunkier, more rustic texture.</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1777427835764"><strong class="schema-faq-question">Can I add raisins or chocolate chips?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Sure! Add up to half a cup of add-ins if you like.</p> </div> </div>


